  chapters:
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'This message concerning Nineveh came as a vision to Nahum, who lived
        in Elkosh.  '
      comments: []
    - title: "\u2019s Anger against Nineveh"
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is a jealous God,\n\tfilled with
        vengeance and rage.\n\tHe takes revenge on all who oppose him\n\tand continues
        to rage against his enemies!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is slow to get angry, but his power
        is great,\n\tand he never lets the guilty go unpunished.\n\tHe displays his
        power in the whirlwind and the storm.\n\tThe billowing clouds are the dust
        beneath his feet.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "At his command the oceans dry up,\n\tand the rivers disappear.\n\tThe
        lush pastures of Bashan and Carmel fade,\n\tand the green forests of Lebanon
        wither.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In his presence the mountains quake,\n\tand the hills melt away;\n\tthe
        earth trembles,\n\tand its people are destroyed.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Who can stand before his fierce anger?\n\tWho can survive his burning
        fury?\n\tHis rage blazes forth like fire,\n\tand the mountains crumble to
        dust in his presence.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is good,\n\ta strong refuge when
        trouble comes.\n\tHe is close to those who trust in him.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But he will sweep away his enemies[COMMENT[0]]in an overwhelming
        flood.\n\tHe will pursue his foes\n\tinto the darkness of night.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:8 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'As in Greek version; Hebrew reads '
          body: sweep away her place.
    - title: 
      content: "Why are you scheming against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t?\n\tHe
        will destroy you with one blow;\n\the won\u2019t need to strike twice!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "His enemies, tangled like thornbushes\n\tand staggering like drunks,\n\twill
        be burned up like dry stubble in a field.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Who is this wicked counselor of yours\n\twho plots evil against the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\n\t\u201CThough
        the Assyrians have many allies,\n\tthey will be destroyed and disappear.\n\tO
        my people, I have punished you before,\n\tbut I will not punish you again.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Now I will break the yoke of bondage from your neck\n\tand tear off
        the chains of Assyrian oppression.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says concerning
        the Assyrians in Nineveh:\n\t\u201CYou will have no more children to carry
        on your name.\n\tI will destroy all the idols in the temples of your gods.\n\tI
        am preparing a grave for you\n\tbecause you are despicable!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  [COMMENT[1]]Look! A messenger is coming over the mountains with
        good news!\n\tHe is bringing a message of peace.\n\tCelebrate your festivals,
        O people of Judah,\n\tand fulfill all your vows,\n\tfor your wicked enemies
        will never invade your land again.\n\tThey will be completely destroyed!"
      comments:
      - number: 
        contents:
        - ft: '  '
          body: 
      - number: '1:15 '
        contents:
        - ft: '  '
          body: 
