  - verses:
    - title: The Fall of Nineveh
      content: "  [COMMENT[1]]Your enemy is coming to crush you, Nineveh.\n\tMan
        the ramparts! Watch the roads!\n\tPrepare your defenses! Call out your forces!  "
      comments:
      - number: 
        contents:
        - ft: '  '
          body: 
      - number: '2:1 '
        contents:
        - ft: '  '
          body: 
        - ft: Verses 2:1-13 are numbered 2:2-14 in Hebrew text.
          body: 
        - ft: '  '
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "Even though the destroyer has destroyed Judah,\n\tthe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will restore its honor.\n\tIsrael\u2019s vine has been stripped of branches,\n\tbut
        he will restore its splendor.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Shields flash red in the sunlight!\n\tSee the scarlet uniforms of
        the valiant troops!\n\tWatch as their glittering chariots move into position,\n\twith
        a forest of spears waving above them.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:3 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek and Syriac versions read '
          body: into position, / the horses whipped into a frenzy.
    - title: 
      content: "The chariots race recklessly along the streets\n\tand rush wildly
        through the squares.\n\tThey flash like firelight\n\tand move as swiftly
        as lightning.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The king shouts to his officers;\n\tthey stumble in their haste,\n\trushing
        to the walls to set up their defenses.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The river gates have been torn open!\n\tThe palace is about to collapse!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Nineveh\u2019s exile has been decreed,\n\tand all the servant girls
        mourn its capture.\n\tThey moan like doves\n\tand beat their breasts in sorrow.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Nineveh is like a leaking water reservoir!\n\tThe people are slipping
        away.\n\t\u201CStop, stop!\u201D someone shouts,\n\tbut no one even looks
        back.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Loot the silver!\n\tPlunder the gold!\n\tThere\u2019s no end to Nineveh\u2019s
        treasures\u2014\n\tits vast, uncounted wealth.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Soon the city is plundered, empty, and ruined.\n\tHearts melt and
        knees shake.\n\tThe people stand aghast,\n\ttheir faces pale and trembling.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Where now is that great Nineveh,\n\tthat den filled with young lions?\n\tIt
        was a place where people\u2014like lions and their cubs\u2014\n\twalked freely
        and without fear.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The lion tore up meat for his cubs\n\tand strangled prey for his
        mate.\n\tHe filled his den with prey,\n\this caverns with his plunder.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI am your enemy!\u201D\n\tsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies.\n\t\u201CYour chariots will soon go up in smoke.\n\tYour
        young men[COMMENT[0]] will be killed in battle.\n\tNever again will you plunder
        conquered nations.\n\tThe voices of your proud messengers will be heard no
        more.\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: '2:13 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: young lions.
  - verses:
    - title: "\u2019s Judgment against Nineveh"
      content: "What sorrow awaits Nineveh,\n\tthe city of murder and lies!\n\tShe
        is crammed with wealth\n\tand is never without victims.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Hear the crack of whips,\n\tthe rumble of wheels!\n\tHorses\u2019
        hooves pound,\n\tand chariots clatter wildly.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "See the flashing swords and glittering spears\n\tas the charioteers
        charge past!\n\tThere are countless casualties,\n\theaps of bodies\u2014\n\tso
        many bodies that\n\tpeople stumble over them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "All this because Nineveh,\n\tthe beautiful and faithless city,\n\tmistress
        of deadly charms,\n\tenticed the nations with her beauty.\n\tShe taught them
        all her magic,\n\tenchanting people everywhere.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI am your enemy!\u201D\n\tsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies.\n\t\u201CAnd now I will lift your skirts\n\tand
        show all the earth your nakedness and shame.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will cover you with filth\n\tand show the world how vile you really
        are.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "All who see you will shrink back and say,\n\t\u2018Nineveh lies in
        ruins.\n\tWhere are the mourners?\u2019\n\tDoes anyone regret your destruction?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Are you any better than the city of Thebes,[COMMENT[0]]situated on
        the Nile River, surrounded by water?\n\tShe was protected by the river on
        all sides,\n\twalled in by water.  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:8 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'No-amon; '
        - ft: also in 3:10.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "Ethiopia[COMMENT[0]] and the land of Egypt\n\tgave unlimited assistance.\n\tThe
        nations of Put and Libya\n\twere among her allies.  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:9 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: Cush.
    - title: 
      content: "Yet Thebes fell,\n\tand her people were led away as captives.\n\tHer
        babies were dashed to death\n\tagainst the stones of the streets.\n\tSoldiers
        threw dice[COMMENT[0]] to get Egyptian officers as servants.\n\tAll their
        leaders were bound in chains.  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:10 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: They cast lots.
    - title: 
      content: "And you, Nineveh, will also stagger like a drunkard.\n\tYou will
        hide for fear of the attacking enemy.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "All your fortresses will fall.\n\tThey will be devoured like the
        ripe figs\n\tthat fall into the mouths\n\tof those who shake the trees.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Your troops will be as weak\n\tand helpless as women.\n\tThe gates
        of your land will be opened wide to the enemy\n\tand set on fire and burned.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Get ready for the siege!\n\tStore up water!\n\tStrengthen the defenses!\n\tGo
        into the pits to trample clay,\n\tand pack it into molds,\n\tmaking bricks
        to repair the walls.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But the fire will devour you;\n\tthe sword will cut you down.\n\tThe
        enemy will consume you like locusts,\n\tdevouring everything they see.\n\tThere
        will be no escape,\n\teven if you multiply like swarming locusts.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Your merchants have multiplied\n\tuntil they outnumber the stars.\n\tBut
        like a swarm of locusts,\n\tthey strip the land and fly away.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Your guards[COMMENT[0]] and officials are also like swarming locusts\n\tthat
        crowd together in the hedges on a cold day.\n\tBut like locusts that fly
        away when the sun comes up,\n\tall of them will fly away and disappear.  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:17 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: princes.
    - title: 
      content: "Your shepherds are asleep, O Assyrian king;\n\tyour princes lie dead
        in the dust.\n\tYour people are scattered across the mountains\n\twith no
        one to gather them together.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "There is no healing for your wound;\n\tyour injury is fatal.\n\tAll
        who hear of your destruction\n\twill clap their hands for joy.\n\tWhere can
        anyone be found\n\twho has not suffered from your continual cruelty?"
      comments: []
